univention-grub (5.0.0-10) unstable; urgency=low

  * Make /etc/default/grub a Univention Configuration template. Some grub/*
    UCR variables are now obsolete: (Bug #22115)
    - grub/vga has been replaced by grub/gfxmode (the format is different and
      the variable is initially set to 1024x768, i.e. equivalent to the default
      setting for grub/vga)
    - grub/memtest86 is no longer used, the option to run a memory test is always
      shown
    - grub/groot, grub/root and grub/boot are no longer needed. Grub 2 performs
      automatic parsing of filesystems and partitions and this no longer needs to
      be configured.	    

 -- Moritz Muehlenhoff <muehlenhoff@univention.de>  Fri, 02 Sep 2011 12:31:04 +0200

univention-grub (5.0.0-9) unstable; urgency=low

  * Remove the template for menu.lst, but keep the previous menu.lst file
    If no menu.lst file exists, the grub2 postinst will assume a fresh
    install and if we keep the template around, it will overwrite the
    transition file written by the grub2 postinst  (Bug #22115)

